# Scenario: ESP Terminal Failure DEFANGED by ContinueAnyway (PR1, Session 4fa5a2d4, 2026-05-22)
# Tenant c9787ba2 observed 199/202 sessions failing with esp_terminal_failure, even though
# customers were demonstrably deploying 1200+ devices through the same profile. Real root cause:
# - ESP profile sets BlockInStatusPage=6 (ContinueAnyway=true)
# - DeviceSetup completes Apps successfully
# - Windows transitions to AccountSetup (esp_phase_changed)
# - Then Windows writes DeviceSetup.Certificates=failed AFTER AccountSetup has already started
# - V2 reducer fired EspTerminalFailure → Failed, even though the device kept progressing
#
# PR1 defang: when ContinueAnyway=true AND AccountSetupEnteredUtc is set, the reducer downgrades
# the EspTerminalFailure to an esp_failure_advisory effect; stage stays at EspAccountSetup,
# EspAdvisoryFailureRecordedUtc is set, monitoring continues. The session never reaches Failed
# in this replay (it would normally complete via Desktop+Hello in production — not modeled here).
#
# Coverage: validates that the engine produces the advisory effect end-to-end through the same
# signal stream the real session 4fa5a2d4 saw.
